The paper deals with motion planning for a robot, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also introduces a new method that combines two paradigms, one of which is optimization-based motion planning, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with controlling a robot, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). The paper uses machine learning techniques to improve motion planning efficiency, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a 7-DOF manipulator, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves analyzing images or video to control the robot.
